{"blocks":[{"key":"5qqn1","text":"Open field chambers were set on a work table in MTF behavior room.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5r781","text":"Velcro squares were applied to the floor of each open field chamber towards the back wall. (12 cm from the back and side walls so that objects adhered to the Velcro would be equidistant from each other and leave space around the object for the rats to explore)  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":260,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"eu4fc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"F3BF5EA04F4B11EDAB18BBDEC888B108","height":225,"id":305195,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8t50o","text":"NOR set up image created in BioRender (2/15/22) by Alicia Avelar","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"NOR test set up, Biorender fig, AJA, 10-18-22.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbpba6rx.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbmba6rx.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbnba6rx.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbkba6rx.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"66r7t","text":"a video camera was mounted to the ceiling above the open field chamber and a long power cord was used to reach the wall outlet. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3pcrp","text":"The power cord was taped in place to the wall near the outlet and the ceiling near the video camera to reduce shaking of the camera during recording from cord weight. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b01fk","text":"All rats were handled prior to tests.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"doer4","text":"Rats were brought into behavior room and given 1 hr habituation time in the room in home cages. For collection of NOR test intoxication data rats spent at least 3 hours in the ethanol vapor self-administration (EVSA) chambers immediately before NOR testing began.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"76hac","text":"2 identical objects are placed in the open field chamber, attached to the Velcro on the chamber floor.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b0jto","text":"First rat is placed in the chamber, centered and close to the front wall (opposite the objects), facing the objects.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ufsl","text":"This is the sample phase and the rat is given 10 minutes to freely explore the open field chamber and objects. Vase shaped objects were used for the sample phase.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":162,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"c2ink","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"278404004F4E11EDAB18BBDEC888B108","height":289,"id":305199,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"76a71","text":"NOR test experimental design. (Cruz-Sanchez et al., 2020)","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"NOR design, Cruz-Sanchez et al., 2020.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbtba6rx.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbrba6rx.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbsba6rx.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jkbqba6rx.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"754s2","text":"Next, is the retention interval (RI).  The retention interval is the time between the end of the sample phase and the beginning of the test phase. We have used 2 retention intervals for the NOR test: 1 minute (to test short term memory) and 24 hours (to test long term memory).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"19hsf","text":"At the end of the sample phase, the rat is removed from the open field chamber.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ud3j","text":"The objects are replaced with one object identical to those present in the sample phase (left side) and a novel object (right side). One vase and one twizzler object were used during the RI 1 minute test phase.  One vase and one plumbob object were used during the RI 24 hours test phase.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"15lk6","text":"After the RI, the rat is placed into the open field chamber for the test phase.  There is one familiar object and one novel object in the chamber during the test phase.  The test phase lasts for 10 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8fffi","text":"When the test phase ends the rat is place back into their home cage and testing continues with other rats in the cohort until complete for each RI.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c9i03","text":"Objects and open field chambers were cleaned and dried with Airx44 disinfectant cleaner and paper towels between tests and sexes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dc4mj","text":"Use anymaze for video behavior tracking and data collection. (I made an anymaze protocol to analyze NOR data from videos)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"18ktq","text":"Use excel to create an electronic record of human tallied data and anymaze data and do further data analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5lkos","text":"Use graphpad prism for graphing and statistical tests.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8cmjs","text":"Noldus ebook behavior basics has information on NOR test data to graph. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2tmrf","text":"“The most important results from the novel object or novel location test include the exploration times of the objects and the frequency of each object exploration. These are generally expressed as the percentage of exploration time spent on novel object:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6vkql","text":"Time spent exploring novel object (x 100)/ Time spent exploring any object","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6lkaq","text":"The preference for novelty is a positive value if there is preference for novelty, and is zero if there is no preference:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
